{
  "texts": [
    "Amongst these identified gaps, the DSA emerged from increasing concerns around disinformation, illegal hate speech, terrorist material, and other forms of legal but harmful content proliferating online.Structurally, the DSA seeks to harmonize the digital single marketfoot_5 by standardizing intermediary services' responsibilities and liabilities across the EU.",
    "It provides graduated obligations proportionate to entities' size, risk-posing capacities, and role in dissemination based on categorizing intermediaries into several classes with distinct duties.",
    "The graduated obligations follow a risk-based approach, with more stringent duties on very large platforms demonstrating high risks.",
    "Through transparency, accountability and due diligence obligations, the DSA aims to ensure online platforms mitigate systemic risks emerging from their activities, design and business models.",
    "Categorization of online entitiesA core feature of the DSA is the asymmetrical obligations imposed, differentiated according to the categories of online intermediaries."
  ]
}